dismissalText.commentary: Mahela Jayawardene lbw b Shoaib Malik 54 (64b 3x4 0x6 101m) SR: 84.37

dismissalComment.html: Mahela has been given out lbw and he doesn't seem to be too happy with the decision. Reason? There was a bottom edge there. Hence the reaction from Mahela. It was a flighted off break around off stump and Mahela went for the reverse sweep and edged it to his pad. A fine innings but it's over now. Vital moment this. 150 for 4. The game could tilt either way now. Will Pakistan get ahead or will Sri Lanka move on?

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan c Umar Amin b Mohammad Asif 18 (25b 3x4 0x6 42m) SR: 72

dismissalComment.html: Now it's the turn of Asif to smile. Courtesy a fab catch from Umar Amin. It was a gentle length delivery outside off and Dilshan goes for the on-the-up square drive. The ball flies and dips to the left of cover point where Amin dives to take it inches of the turf. It was dying on him and well to the left but he flung himself and got his palms under the ball. The Sri Lankan openers are back in the hut. The old firm of Sanga and Mahela are in.

dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi c Sangakkara b Muralidaran 109 (76b 8x4 7x6 130m) SR: 143.42

dismissalComment.html: What a catch. Stunning reflex from Sanga but stand up and applaud for Shahid Afridi. What a treat to watch. What a special knock. It was a ripping off break that turned and bounced into Afridi who trying to back away for the cut shot. He ended up jabbing it of his gloves to right of the keeper. Sanga was moving his hands to outside leg, coverin for the original trajectory, but reacts very quickly to lunge across to his right and behind him to take a stunner. A special innings took a very good delivery and a special catch to come to an end.

dismissalComment.html: What a fabulicious delivery! too good for Aamer! It was full in length, landed on the off and middle and Aamer actually tried his best to defend it and get some bat on it. But the ball shaped away late to hit the off stump. Waqar Younis stares on from the dressing room. Nervous tension in that camp.

headshotImage.caption: Shoaib Akhtar player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shoaib Akhtar player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: What an awesome slower one delivery from Malinga! For sure, Shoaib wasn't expecting. He was probably thinking of a yorker. Even a bouncer. And there comes a lovely loopy dipping slower one. Shoaib is stunned, gets forward and just pushes out at it. Checks his shot. And the ball lobs towards mid-off. Malinga roars. And they then they were one. What a game this has been. What will happen now? Oh what drama. What a roller-coaster ride. What tension

headshotImage.caption: Mohammad Asif player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Asif player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Would you believe it? Malinga had one delivery at Asif. Just one delivery. It was to be the end of his spell. And what does he do? He fires it on a length, it lands on the middle and it moves towards off and middle line. Asif didn't have the skill to cope with it. His back leg was moving towards leg stump even as he stabbed in thin air. Leather on wood. Clatter! Game over! Spare a thought for Shahid Afridi. What a great innings it was but he had to finish up on the losing side.

commentPreTextItems.html: Subir: "How easy it is commenting. You say Razzaq should have taken initiative. If Razzaq HAD taken initiative when Afridi was wobbling you'd say - "Why did he need to do it. Afridi was hitting. He only needed to get support""

commentTextItems.html: Would you believe it? Malinga had one delivery at Asif. Just one delivery. It was to be the end of his spell. And what does he do? He fires it on a length, it lands on the middle and it moves towards off and middle line. Asif didn't have the skill to cope with it. His back leg was moving towards leg stump even as he stabbed in thin air. Leather on wood. Clatter! Game over! Spare a thought for Shahid Afridi. What a great innings it was but he had to finish up on the losing side.

commentPostTextItems.html: The crowd roar and roar. Shoaib Akthar impressed on his comeback. Shahid Afridi dazzled with an special out-of-character knock. But it was Lasith Malinga who killed the contest with an outstanding effort with the ball. Stats say that it was his career-best spell. And remember, he chipped in with a vital contribution with the bat as well.
Also don't forget Angelo Mathews' responsible innings and Kumar Sangakkara's special catch to dismiss Shahid Afridi. That set the cat among the pigeons.
Hang on for the quotes from the ceremony
Sri: "Malinga scored 16, the margin of victory"
Dan Pettitt: "Lasith Malinga achieved his best ODI score with the bat (surpassing 15) and his best ODI bowling (formely 4/28). Good game."

Salman Butt (Afrdi is injured and hasn't come out) : "It was fantatic to see the courage and heart he [Afridi] showed in the middle. I wish we could have won the match. Even if this last ball had gone to Razzaq, we would have won it. It was a very chase-able target. Shahid bhai and Umar brought us back. It was a double-paced wicket. Sometimes it would come to you and sometimes it would stop on you. Afridi is getting better; he was cramping all over."
Salman Butt also collects the man of the match trophy on behalf Shahid Afridi.

Sangakkara: "We were driver's seat twice in the game - when we and Mahela were batting and then we had bowled 18 overs. Afridi .. it was the best I have seen him bat. It was a great knock. Kulasekara, Angelo bowled very well and then Lasith Malinga came in and looked as if he would get wicket every over. Maharoof did well. Afridi played really well. then Malinga came and did a brilliant job. It was a catch-22 for me whether to give Murali a over to Afridi. He is the best spinner in the world. It's very rare that he gives so many runs. All credit to Afridi for playing a special knock. Angelo Mathews batted really well and Malinga too contributed in the end. We probably did the basics well in patches but we have to pretty ruthless .. when we have down like this we should finish it off."

That's it from us. I will leave you with a comment from a reader - Radical Zee: "Talk about being the perfect marketing tool to support the case for the survival of the 50-over game. What a contest! Hats off to both the teams. Such a Pakistan recovery would have never been possible in a T20 game. Such a magnificent death over spell would never been possible in a T20 4-over spell. 50-over game is the right time for an absorbing contest. Believe it or not."

A special innings took a very good delivery and a special catch to come to an end.

What a great innings it was but he had to finish up on the losing side.

dismissalComment.html: Umar is run out by Dilshan. It was pushed towards short cover point and he set for a risky single. Afridi sends him back. dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi c Sangakkara b Muralidaran 109 (76b 8x4 7x6 130m) SR: 143.42

dismissalComment.html: What a catch. Stunning reflex from Sanga but stand up and applaud for Shahid Afridi. What a treat to watch. What a special knock. It was a ripping off break that turned and bounced into Afridi who trying to back away for the cut shot. He ended up jabbing it of his gloves to right of the keeper. Sanga was moving his hands to outside leg, coverin for the original trajectory, but reacts very quickly to lunge across to his right and behind him to take a stunner. A special innings took a very good delivery and a special catch to come to an end.

dismissalText.commentary: Shoaib Akhtar c Mathews b Malinga 1 (2b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: What an awesome slower one delivery from Malinga! For sure, Shoaib wasn't expecting. He was probably thinking of a yorker. Even a bouncer. And there comes a lovely loopy dipping slower one. Shoaib is stunned, gets forward and just pushes out at it. Checks his shot. And the ball lobs towards mid-off. Malinga roars. And they then they were one. What a game this has been. What will happen now? Oh what drama. What a roller-coaster ride. What tension

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Asif b Malinga 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Would you believe it? Malinga had one delivery at Asif. Just one delivery. It was to be the end of his spell. And what does he do? He fires it on a length, it lands on the middle and it moves towards off and middle line. Asif didn't have the skill to cope with it. His back leg was moving towards leg stump even as he stabbed in thin air. Leather on wood. Clatter! Game over! Spare a thought for Shahid Afridi. What a great innings it was but he had to finish up on the losing side.
